Class SimpleFileParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.gmit.dip.AbstractFileParser<java.lang.String>
      • ie.gmit.dip.SimpleFileParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractParser<ParsableFile,​java.lang.String>
    public class SimpleFileParser
extends AbstractFileParser<java.lang.String>
    The class SimpleFileParser is an concrete type which extends the abstract base type AbstractFileParser by fully implementing a parse functionality. The key functionality is that it allows one to parse any ParsableFile to a string, with appropriate exception handling implemented. This class, and the cohesive ParsableFile class are potentially of use as generic parsers in a wide variety of projects and APIs as a hierarchy of specialized parsers.

        public java.lang.String parse()

        Method which parses a file line by line and returns a String with appropriate error-catching and exception throwing. The running time of the parse method scales as O(n) where n is the number of lines in the file to be parsed.
